HEADWORD: Amphictyony
<hw>Am*phic"ty*o*ny</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Amphictyonies</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[Gr. <?/.]</ety> <fld>(Grecian Hist.)</fld> <def>A league of states
of ancient Greece; esp. the celebrated confederation known as the
Amphictyonic Council. Its object was to maintain the common interests of
Greece.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

